At our last wedding of the season, it didn’t just rain…it POURED.  Man we had to work hard and think on our feet to bring it all to life, but it was so worth it - the day was incredible.  From the last-minute ceremony tent to re-designing the layout and bringing in all the umbrellas and blankets, it was an unforgettable night (and amazing dance party!). 

It’s weekends like this that remind me time and time again how important it is to have a GOOD TEAM backing each event.  Anyone should be able to perform well when things are going to plan, but the real test is when things start shifting unexpectedly…a good team is worth their weight in gold.

One of the absolute highlights of my year was discovering the amazing town of Ravello, on the Amalfi Coast in Italy.  If you haven’t been, put it on your bucket list.  I can’t wait to go back.  From wandering the romantic cobblestone streets to dining at @michelin restaurants, it was AMAZING.  A few recs:

1) stay at @belmondhotelcaruso.  The infinity pool, incredible accommodations, the service, the views, and the food…oh my goodness the food.  One of the best places @bebravespeier and I have ever stayed!

2) explore the gardens at @villacimbrone - and take it all in at the Terrace of Infinity. 

3) olive oil tasting in the town square 

4) spa at @belmondhotelcaruso 

5) Lunch at Osteria Ravello

We worked with @wedawaystravel to plan this stay - and it was amazing!

What a weird week.  Friends, we show lots of the amazing work we get to do here on the gram.  And as amazing as entrepreneurship can be, there can be huge unexpected challenges.  On Monday, our offices/floral studio (fondly named “HQ” by my kids) was completely flooded.  So much water damage, and So. Much. Mud. 

Thankfully, most of our design/inventory/floral mechanics were safely stored up high on shelves, and anything damaged is replaceable.  We are still wrapping our heads around the water damage and what that looks like in the coming weeks.
And our team is still working hard and making all event planning things happen.

Ultimately, I am just so thankful nobody was hurt or working in the office during the flood. I am thankful that I just happened to “re-sort” my vases and candles last week and put them up high on the shelves.  I am thankful we don’t have any events this month so we can problem solve before we’re in production mode. And I’m thankful that me and my team know how to navigate unexpected situations with peace, joy, and flexibility. 

Definitely an unexpected “dose of real life…”

Wow! Thank you @californiaweddingday (and all our local industry partners) for naming us BEST OVERALL VENDOR in Santa Barbara for 2023! 

I am so incredibly humbled and honored. I remember starting this business as a hobby to help pay for college. I remember doing flowers in my living room with my kids and staying up all night to produce weddings after working my 9-5 job. I remember quitting my full-time job and taking a leap of faith to grow this business. I remember our first full wedding build out, the first full time hire, moving in to a studio space and out of our garage…it has been such an adventure.  I am so incredibly thankful to be where we are now…producing trend-setting events around the globe…what the heck?!

A huge thank you to our clients for believing in us and trusting us to come alongside you for life milestone celebrations.  Thank you to all our industry partners who work alongside us to bring these events to life.

And most importantly, thank you to my team - your hard work, creativity, humor, dedication, and passion for what we do is unmatched. I am so thankful to each one of you.  And especially to @cassandragray (pictured with me at the gala) - you are such an incredible planner and your hard work makes all of the logistics come together at each and every event.  I am so thankful for your leadership and dedication. 

And to my wife, partner, and co-business owner - @bebravespeier - I love you.  From when we started dating in high school to over a decade of growing this company together (with kids, marriage, and all sorts of real life curveballs in between)…look how far we’ve come 😊

We’ve all felt “lost” or not known where to be as a guest at an event.  It’s the worst, right?! 

In order to feel comfortable and present, it’s important that communication is clear for your guests. 

From the moment your guests arrive, our team is stationed to welcome your loved ones.  Two people welcome at the ceremony, assisting any elderly guests and ensuring everyone feels comfortable.  Then, two of us are working with the bridal party and immediate family, lining everyone up, helping with any fashion emergencies, triple checking each jacket is buttoned correctly, and ensuring everyone is feeling peaceful, joyful, and flexible.  We line up the bridal party, help with the bridal gown, cue the musicians, and the wedding begins!  Meanwhile, other members of the team are putting final touches on the reception and ensuring each vendor knows where to be and when. 

After the ceremony, our team guides your guests to cocktail hour, helps them find their seats for dinner, and is present to ensure any questions or needs are addressed.  Whether it’s locating the nearest restroom or helping a guest determine where to make a dinner reservation the next day, we love guiding your guests through the wedding experience so that you can be fully present and enjoy your own day. 

Of course, there is so much more we do behind the scenes…handling unexpected circumstances, family dynamics, weather shifts, and making “game day” decisions to ensure everything goes smoothly.  Personally, I love the adrenaline of an event day, and I love seeing our team’s hard work come to life.

Pro tip: live entertainment (especially a band) is an incredible way to infuse more energy and personalization in to your wedding day.  If you are hiring a band, a few things to pay attention to: 

✅ check the contract for all of the requirements - power needs, a green room, meal requirements, breaks, shade, lighting, etc. 

✅ determine the time of the sound check.  If you are having the ceremony and reception in one location, you don’t want the band checking sound as you are walking down the aisle! You may need to pay for an early sound check to ensure everyone is ready before the guests arrive 

✅ if you have special song requests, communicate them with the band early, especially if it’s a song the band needs to learn
